Estimator()\\n\\n    # Example code to analyze\\n    example_code = \\"\\"\\"\\ndef example_function():\\n    print(\'Hello, World!\')\\n\\"\\"\\"\\n    analysis_results = code_analyzer.analyze_code(example_code)\\n    print(\'Code Analysis Results:\', analysis_results)\\n\\n    # Example tasks\\n    task_manager.add_task(\'task1\')\\n    task_manager.add_task(\'task2\', dependencies=[\'task1\'])\\n    task_manager.add_task(\'task3\', dependencies=[\'task2\'])\\n\\n    # Example build time estimation\\n    tasks_to_build = [\'task1\', \'task2\', \'task3\']\\n    estimated_time = build_estimator.estimate_build_time(tasks_to_build)\\n    print(\'Estimated Build Time:\', estimated_time, \'seconds\')"\n}\n```\n\nThis `solution.py` file includes the basic structure and components for the `Collaborative Build Optimizer (CBO)` system, with placeholder logic for code analysis, task management, and build time estimation. The actual implementation details for these components would need to be filled in based on the specific requirements and use cases of the project.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': [], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}, {'iteration': 3, 'task_assignments': {'agent1': 'Given the task history and the current state, the next step is to delegate the task of revising the code to Agent 2, as you have already created the initial implementation in `solution.py`. Since the initial code has been created and the memory reflects that, the next logical step is to instruct Agent 2 to revise the code.\n\nHere is the action you should take to delegate the task to Agent 2:\n\n```json\n{\n  "type": "action_function_call",\n  "action_name": "delegate_task",\n  "args": {\n    "agent_name": "agent2",\n    "task_description": "Revise the code in solution.py to add any missing functions and improve the initial implementation.",\n    "file_path": "C:\\\\Users\\\\70454\\\\Desktop\\\\PredictDesign\\\\results\\\\parallel_api_test\\\\runtime_configs\\\\coding\\\\t